:h2 name=CHCP.CHCP - Change the current code page
:parml compact tsize=12 break=fit.
:pt.:hp3.Purpose&colon.:ehp3.:pd.Display or change the current system code page.
.br
:pt.:hp3.Format&colon.:ehp3.:pd.:hp2.CHCP [:ehp2.:hp3.n:ehp3. :hp2.]:ehp2.
.br
:pt.:pd.:hp3.n :ehp3.&colon. A system code page number.
:eparml.:p.
:hp2.Usage:ehp2.
:p.
Code page switching allows you to select different character sets
for language support.
:p.
If you enter CHCP without a number, the current code page is
displayed.
:xmp.
    [c&colon.\] chcp
    Active code page&colon. 437
:exmp.:p.
If you enter CHCP plus a code page number, the system code page is
changed. For example, to set the code page to multilingual&colon.
:xmp.
    [c&colon.\] chcp 850
:exmp.:p.
CHCP only affects the current &4OS2. session, and any new programs started
from within that session; the active code page in other sessions remains
unchanged.
:p.
CHCP accepts one of the prepared system code pages. An error
message is displayed if a code page is selected that has not been
prepared for the system.
:p.
See your OS/2 documentation for more information on CHCP.

