:h1 nosearch name=TOC_ConfigurationNotebook.Configuration Notebook
:p.
The Configuration Notebook is a standard WPS settings notebook which allows you
to modify the most common &4OS2. options.
:p.
Each page includes the following buttons at the bottom&colon.
:lm margin=8.:parml compact tsize=16 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.Save:ehp2.:pd.Save the current settings and continue editing.
:pt.:hp2.OK:ehp2.:pd.Save the current settings and exit the dialog.
:pt.:hp2.Cancel:ehp2.:pd.Discard the current changes and exit the dialog.
:pt.:hp2.Help:ehp2.:pd.Open this help guide to this section.
:eparml.
:p.
The Configuration Notebook consists of the following pages&colon.
:lm margin=8.:parml compact tsize=4 break=fit.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=StartupOption.Startup:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=DisplayOption.Display:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CommandLine1Option.Command Line 1:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CommandLine2Option.Command Line 2:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=Options1.Options:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=Options2.Options:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CommandsOption.Commands:elink.
:eparml.:lm margin=1.

