.* --------------------------------------------------------------------------

:h1 name=WhatsNew.What's New? - Change History
:p.
This section provides a comprehensive list of what's changed since our
previous major release, version 2.52. Maintenance changes made between
versions 3.00 and &10ver. are indicated notes in the left margin (such as
:hp2.&4ver.:ehp2.). :hp8.Changes after version &4verprev. were not made by JP 
Software.:ehp8. 
:p.
This topic does not explain how to use each new feature. Instead, where
appropriate we have provided links below to the detailed help topics
containing additional usage information or other documentation.
:p.
Some of the descriptions here may be more detailed than you need; if you
aren't using a feature, feel free to skip to the next item.
:p.
This topic is divided into the following subtopics&colon.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=4 compact break=fit.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewGen.General Features and Enhancements:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewCmdLine.Line Editing and History:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewCommands.Command Changes:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewVars.Variables and Variable Functions:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewStartup.Startup and Configuration:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewCompat.Technical and Compatibility
Enhancements:elink.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=NewBugs.Bugs Fixed:elink.
:eparml.:lm margin=1.
:p.
The major new features in the last JP Software release include&colon.
:lm margin=4.:parml tsize=4 break=fit.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=ExtDirSearch.Extended Directory
Searches:elink.&colon. allow you to change to a directory anywhere on your
system by entering only part of its name. They must be explicitly enabled
before you can use them. See :link reftype=hd refid=DirNav.Directory
Navigation:elink. for complete details.
:pt.:pd.New :link reftype=hd refid=ExclRanges.File Exclusion
Ranges:elink.&colon. provide a convenient way to exclude files from any
internal command -- faster and more flexible than using EXCEPT.
:pt.:pd.The new :link reftype=hd refid=BatchDebug.Batch File
Debugger:elink. can execute each line step by step, process or trace into
additional batch files, and display variables, aliases, and expanded commands
at each step.
:pt.:pd.:hp2.New commands:ehp2. include&colon.
:parml tsize=4 break=fit.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=OPTION.OPTION:elink.&colon. Offers
complete configuration adjustment, either through interactive dialogs or on
the command line.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=SWITCH.SWITCH:elink.&colon. Provides
for "case" statements in batch files.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=TOUCH.TOUCH:elink.&colon. Adjusts file
dates and times.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=TREE.TREE:elink.&colon. Displays the
directory tree, with or without filenames, in a variety of formats.
:eparml.
:eparml.:lm margin=1.

.* --------------------------------------------------------------------------

:h2 name=NewGen.General Features and Enhancements
:p.
:hp2.What's New - General Features and Enhancements:ehp2.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver. :ehp2. :pd.The default location for :hp1.JPSTREE.IDX:ehp1. has
been changed to the &4OS2. installation directory (if writable) or to the root of
the boot volume. This location is written to the TreePath variable in &4OS2INI..
If :hp1.JPSTREE.IDX:ehp1. already exists, it is left in place.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver. :ehp2. :pd.Add the Shift-Ins key combinations as an 
option to paste text.
:eparml.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made by JP Software prior to version 3.01:ehp8.
:pt.:pd.Added a complete batch file debugger. The debugger displays the
batch file in a window and allows you to execute each line step by step,
process or trace into additional batch files and subroutines, and display
variables and aliases at each step. See :link reftype=hd
refid=BatchDebug.Batch File Debugging:elink. for complete details.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=Popup.Popup windows:elink. (for filename
completion, command history recall, etc.) now allow you to search for
a line within the window contents by typing the first few characters of the
line. The search string is displayed in the lower right corner of the window.
:pt.:pd.You can now :link reftype=hd refid=Redirection.redirect:elink. to
and from the clipboard by using the pseudo-device name CLIP&colon.&per. For
example, to redirect DIR to the clipboard&colon.
:xmp.
    dir *.doc > clip&colon.
:exmp.
:pt.:pd.The :link reftype=hd refid=HelpSys.online help:elink. has
been reorganized to make it easier to navigate through the main topics, and
includes additional reference information, reference tables, and a
glossary.
:pt.:pd.The default maximum :link reftype=hd refid=DESCRIBE.file
description:elink. length is now 511 bytes in all products.
:pt.:pd.Two new characters can now follow the :link reftype=hd
refid=Escape.escape character:elink.&colon. An escape followed by
a 'q' will substitute a double quote; an escape followed by a 'k' will
substitute a back quote.
:pt.:pd.The decimal and thousands characters used in :link reftype=hd
refid=_@EVAL.@EVAL:elink. and in displayed version numbers and other similar
locations are now controllable with the :link reftype=hd
refid=INI_DecimalChar.DecimalChar:elink. and :link reftype=hd
refid=INI_ThousandsChar.ThousandsChar:elink. directives in the
:link reftype=hd refid=INIFile.&4OS2INI.:elink. file, the corresponding options in the configuration or
OPTION dialogs, and the SETDOS /G command. These characters are saved by
SETLOCAL and restored by ENDLOCAL. This is intended as an aid to those
writing batch files which perform arithmetic operations and which may be
used in countries with differing separator characters.
:pt.:pd.The directory stack size used by :link reftype=hd
refid=PUSHD.PUSHD:elink. and :link reftype=hd refid=POPD.POPD:elink. has
been increased from 255 to 511 bytes to leave adequate room for long
directory names.
:pt.:pd.:hp1..BTM:ehp1. files can now be longer than 64K bytes, though
compressed :hp1..BTMs:ehp1. still have to be less than 64K.
:eparml.:lm margin=1.

.* --------------------------------------------------------------------------

:h2 name=NewCmdLine.Command Line Editing
:p.
:hp2.What's New - Command Line Editing:ehp2.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver.:ehp2. :pd.Duplicate entries in 
:link reftype=hd refid=CmdHist.history recall:elink. can be suppressed
by adding :link reftype=hd refid=INI_HistNoDups.HistNoDups:elink.=Yes to the 
INI file. They are not removed from saved histories that contain dups.
:eparml.
:lm margin=6.:parml tsize=3 break=fit. 
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made by JP Software prior to version 3.01:ehp8.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=ExtDirSearch.Extended directory
searches:elink. can be used directly from the command line for quick
directory navigation; see :link reftype=hd refid=AutoDir.Automatic Directory
Changes:elink. or :link reftype=hd refid=DirNav.Directory Navigation:elink.
for details.
:pt.:pd.Made several enhancements to :link reftype=hd
refid=FileComp.filename completion:elink., including&colon.
:parml tsize=4 break=fit.
:pt.*:pd.The Ctrl-A key, which toggles between long and short
filenames for filename completion, can now be hit at any point during command
line entry -- not just during filename completion. For example, if you hit
Ctrl-A at the beginning of the command line, all filenames subsequently
returned for that line will be short names (until you hit Ctrl-A again).
:pt.*:pd.Filename completion can now be customized for individual commands
via the new :link reftype=hd refid=INI_FileCompletion.FileCompletion:elink.
:link reftype=hd refid=INIFile.&4OS2INI.:elink. directive (or environment variable). For example, you can
configure &4OS2. to complete only the names of :hp1..TXT:ehp1. files when the
command line starts with the name of your text editor, or to display only
directory names when you are entering a CD command.
:pt.*:pd.The F7 filename completion popup window now sorts the filename list
alphabetically.
:eparml.
:pt.:pd.You can now expand aliases immediately while still on the command
line with the Ctrl-F key.
:pt.:pd.Command line :link reftype=hd refid=CmdHist.history recall:elink.
will now stop at the beginning and end of the history list rather than
wrapping around, if you set HistWrap to No in :link reftype=hd refid=INIFile.&4OS2INI.:elink. or
through the configuration dialogs.
:eparml.:lm margin=1.

.* --------------------------------------------------------------------------

:h2 name=NewCommands.Command Changes
:p.
:hp2.What's New - Command Changes:ehp2.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver.:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=COPY.COPY:elink.&colon. Added /J switch&colon.
Makes a directory copy behave like CMD. The directory is copied to the target instead of just 
the files in the directory being copied.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver.:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=MOVE.MOVE:elink.&colon. Added /J switch&colon.
Makes a directory move behave like CMD. The directory is moved to the target instead of just 
the files in the directory being moved.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver.:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=DIR.DIR:elink.&colon. Added a DIR switch&colon.
:parml tsize=8 compact break=fit.
:pt.   /Q:pd.Suppress non-fatal errors.
:eparml.
.* 2013-04-25 SHL
:pt.:hp2.&9ver.:ehp2. :pd.Added :link reftype=hd refid=INI_DirHistory.DirHistory:elink. memory usage to :link reftype=hd refid=MEMORY.MEMORY:elink. command output.
.* 2013-09-19 SHL
:pt.:hp2.&9ver.:ehp2. :pd.Added #! as :link reftype=hd refid=EXTPROC.EXTPROC:elink. equivalent if :link reftype=hd refid=INI_UnixPaths.UnixPaths:elink. enabled.
:eparml.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made by JP Software:ehp8..
:eparml.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.3.02:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CD.CD:elink. and
:link reftype=hd refid=CDD.CDD:elink.&colon. Added the :hp2./N:ehp2.
switch to disable extended directory searches and the change directory
popup window (intended primarily for use in batch files).
:pt.:hp2.3.01:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=FFIND.FFIND:elink.&colon. Added support for
piping into FFIND. You can either specify CON for the filename, or if no
filename is specified FFIND will detect whether STDIN is a pipe and use that.
:pt.:hp2.3.01:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=TOUCH.TOUCH:elink.&colon. /T[acw] and
/D[acw] now default to the current date and time. Previously when the "a",
"c", or "w" was specified the date or time had to be specified also.
:eparml.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made prior to version 3.01:ehp8.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=ACTIVATE.ACTIVATE:elink.&colon. This
new command switches to another window.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=ATTRIB.ATTRIB:elink.&colon. Added the /E
switch to disable display of non-fatal errors. Also, ATTRIB now allows
underscores in the attribute string, so that you can get a result from the
%:link reftype=hd refid=_@ATTRIB.@ATTRIB:elink. variable function and feed
it directly to the ATTRIB command.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CD.CD:elink. and :link reftype=hd
refid=CDD.CDD:elink.&colon. Now support extended directory searches, which
allow you to change to a directory anywhere on your system by entering only
part of its name. The CDD /S switch builds the extended directory search
database. Extended directory searches must be explicitly enabled before
you can use them. See :link reftype=hd refid=DirNav.Directory
Navigation:elink. for complete details.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CDD.CDD:elink.&colon. Added the /A switch to
display the current directory for all existing and ready drives from
C&colon. to Z&colon..
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=CHCP.CHCP:elink.&colon. Changed to only affect
the current process and its children, as in :hp1.CMD.EXE:ehp1.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=COPY.COPY:elink.&colon. Added several
switches&colon.
:parml tsize=8 compact break=fit.
:pt.   /E:pd.Disable display of non-fatal errors.
:pt.   /K:pd.Preserve read-only attributes during a COPY.
:pt.   /X:pd.Clear the archive bit from the source file after a successful
copy.
:pt.   /Z:pd.Overwrite read-only target files.
:eparml.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=COPY.COPY:elink.&colon. When copying from a
FAT16 volume to a volume supporting long filenames, COPY will now use the
&per.LONGNAME extended attribute of the source file (if available) to determine the
long name. When copying from HPFS to FAT16, COPY sets the &per.LONGNAME attribute if
possible, to preserve the long name.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=DEL.DEL:elink.&colon. Added two
switches&colon.
:parml tsize=8 compact break=fit.
:pt.   /E:pd.Disable display of non-fatal errors.
:pt.   /W:pd.Clear the file to 0's before deleting it.
:eparml.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=DIR.DIR:elink.&colon. Added or modified
several of the DIR switches&colon.
:parml tsize=8 compact break=fit.
:pt.   /2:pd.Now forces the use of truncated names on HPFS drives.
:pt.   /4:pd.Now forces the use of truncated names on HPFS drives, and displays
files between 1 and 9.9 Mb in tenths (i.e., "2.4M").
:pt.   /G:pd.(New) Displays the allocated size instead of the file size.
:pt.   /W:pd.Now forces the use of truncated names on HPFS drives.
:eparml.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=DIRHISTORY.DIRHISTORY:elink.&colon. This new
command has the same syntax as HISTORY, but it modifies the directory
history.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=DO.DO:elink.&colon. Added two new DO loop
types&colon.
:parml tsize=4 compact break=fit.
:pt.*:pd."DO x IN filename" retrieves each matching filename from a
wildcard spec and inserts the value into the variable.
:pt.*:pd."DO x IN @filename" retrieves each line in the file and inserts it
into the variable.
:eparml.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=ECHO.ECHOERR:elink. and :link reftype=hd
refid=ECHOS.ECHOSERR:elink.&colon. These new commands are like ECHO
and ECHOS, but output goes to the standard error device instead of standard
output.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=ENDLOCAL.ENDLOCAL:elink.&colon. To aid in
making batch files portable, SETLOCAL and ENDLOCAL now save and restore the
command separator, escape character, parameter character, and decimal and
thousands separators.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=FFIND.FFIND:elink.&colon. Added two new
switches&colon.
:parml tsize=8 compact break=fit.
:pt.   /I:pd.Do a literal match even if the text search string contains
wildcard characters.
:pt.   /R:pd.Start searching for text from the end backwards.
:eparml.
:p.
Also, the /X switch will now display the offset in both hex and decimal.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=FOR.FOR:elink.&colon. Added several new
switches for compatibility with Windows NT 4.0's CMD.EXE; see the command
reference information for complete details.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=GOTO.GOTO:elink.&colon. Added support for
Windows NT 4.0's "GOTO &colon.EOF" -- If there is no "&colon.EOF" label,
GOTO ends the current batch file (equivalent to a QUIT).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=IF.IF:elink. / :link reftype=hd
refid=IFF.IFF:elink.&colon. These commands now support nested conditional
tests, with parentheses, e.g.&colon.
:xmp.
    if  (%a == 1 .or. %b == 2) .and. %c == 3 echo something
:exmp.:p.
See the command reference information for complete syntax rules.
:pt.:pd.Added a new "IF DEFINED varname" test, which succeeds if the
specified variable exists in the environment. This is included for
compatibility with Windows NT 4.0's CMD.EXE, and is the same as a test
like&colon.
:xmp.
    if  "%varname" ne "" ...
:exmp.
:pt.:pd.Changed the comparison tests to accept a leading decimal separator
as a numeric character, provided the remainder of the string is numeric and
does not contain additional decimal characters.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=KEYSTACK.KEYSTACK:elink.&colon. This new
command allows you to pass keystrokes to PM and VIO windowed applications
(but not to DOS apps or VIO full-screen sessions).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=LIST.LIST:elink.&colon. Added a range of
enhancements, including&colon.
:parml tsize=4 break=fit.
:pt.*:pd.Ctrl-PgUp and Ctrl-PgDn will go to the previous and next
file in the current group, respectively.
:pt.*:pd.Ctrl-F searches backwards for a text string; Ctrl-N repeats the
last search, searching backwards.
:pt.*:pd.Matching strings on the first page are now highlighted after a search.
:pt.*:pd.When piping output to LIST in most cases you no longer need the /S
switch; for example, to view DIR's output in LIST you can now use&colon.
:xmp.
    dir  | list
:exmp.:p.
Also, added three new switches&colon.
:parml tsize=8 compact break=fit.
:pt.   /I:pd.Ignore case in a /T search.
:pt.   /R:pd.The search initiated by /T goes backwards from the end of the file.
:pt.   /T:pd.Search for text when LIST starts.
:eparml.:eparml.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=MD.MD:elink.&colon. Added the /N switch to
create a directory without updating the extended directory search database
(useful for temporary directories).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=MOVE.MOVE:elink.&colon. Added the /E switch
to disable display of non-fatal errors.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=MOVE.MOVE:elink.&colon. When moving files
from a FAT16 volume to a volume supporting long filenames, MOVE will now use the
&per.LONGNAME extended attribute of the source file (if available) to determine the
long name. When moving files from HPFS to FAT16, MOVE sets the &per.LONGNAME
attribute if possible, to preserve the long name.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=OPTION.OPTION:elink.&colon. This new command
can be used for two purposes. When invoked without parameters, it loads the
:link reftype=hd refid=TOC_ConfigurationNotebook.Configuration Notebook:elink.,
which adjusts most commonly-used settings in the
:link reftype=hd refid=INIFile.&4OS2INI.:elink. file. The pages provide a
convenient method of adjusting configuration without manually editing
:link reftype=hd refid=INIFile.&4OS2INI.:elink.&per. OPTION can
also be used to change specific settings on an individual basis with the
OPTION Name=value ..&per. syntax; see the command for complete details.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=PROMPT.PROMPT:elink.&colon. Added the
:hp2.$+:ehp2. metacharacter, which displays one :hp2.+:ehp2. for each PUSHD
level.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=REN.REN / RENAME:elink.&colon. Added the /E
switch to disable display of non-fatal errors.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=RETURN.RETURN:elink.&colon. Now accepts an
optional argument for the errorlevel to return. The errorlevel can be tested
with %:link reftype=hd refid=_QMARK.?:elink. or :link reftype=hd
refid=IF.IF:elink. ERRORLEVEL.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=SCREEN.SCREEN:elink., :link reftype=hd
refid=SCRPUT.SCRPUT:elink., and :link reftype=hd
refid=VSCRPUT.VSCRPUT:elink.&colon. If you specify 999 for the row, the
text will be centered vertically; if you specify 999 for the column, the
text will be centered horizontally.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=SELECT.SELECT:elink.&colon. You can now type
characters from the start of a filename and the selection bar will jump to
the first matching name. Due to this change, the key to popup :link
reftype=hd refid=LIST.LIST:elink. on the currently selected file has been
changed from L to ^L. Also, added the /T&colon.acw switch to select the
date and time to use for display and sorting on HPFS drives.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=SETLOCAL.SETLOCAL:elink.&colon. To aid in
making batch files portable, SETLOCAL now saves the command separator, escape
character, parameter character, and decimal and thousands separators;
:link reftype=hd refid=ENDLOCAL.ENDLOCAL:elink. restores them.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=SHIFT.SHIFT:elink.&colon. The new "/n"
argument will start the shift at the specified argument -- i.e., "shift /2"
moves %3 to %2, %4 to %3, etc.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=START.START:elink.&colon. Added /LD for a
local directory history list.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=START.START:elink.&colon. Added support for
the (undocumented) Warp 4 CMD.EXE "DosSetting.xxx=yyy" environment variables
to specify settings for DOS sessions.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=SWITCH.SWITCH:elink.&colon. This new command
provides a C-like switch construct for batch files. SWITCH scans each CASE
statement looking for a matching value; if it finds one it executes the block
of code inside that CASE statement, and then jumps to the end of the switch
block (ENDSWITCH). If no CASE statement matches, SWITCH will execute the
code in the (optional) DEFAULT block.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=TITLE.TITLE:elink.&colon. This new command
changes the &4OS2. window title for windowed sessions (it is not effective in
full-screen sessions).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=TOUCH.TOUCH:elink.&colon. This new command
changes the date and/or time for a file or files. You can set a specified
date and time or use the current system clock, and you can optionally change
the last access / creation date and time fields on HPFS drives.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=TREE.TREE:elink.&colon. This new command
displays a graphical directory tree using either line-drawing or ASCII
characters. It can also optionally display filenames, dates, times, and
sizes.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=UNALIAS.UNALIAS:elink.&colon. Added the /R
switch to read a file of aliases to remove.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=UNSET.UNSET:elink.&colon. Added the /R
switch to read a file of variables to remove.
:eparml.

.* --------------------------------------------------------------------------

:h2 name=NewVars.Variables and Functions
:p.
:hp2.What's New - Variables and Functions:ehp2.
Added or updated the following internal variables (all variables listed are
new unless otherwise noted)&colon.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.&10ver.:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_TMSMP._TMSMP:elink.&colon. Returns
the current dat and time (yyyy-mm-dd-hh-mm-ss) The format can be set in the INI using
TmSmpFmt= the year can be 2 or 4 digits, only "-" is allowed as a separator, time is
always ordered hh-mm-ss but leaving off ss will suppress adding seconds to the string.
If TmSmpFmt= is not set the default date format is used.
:eparml.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made by JP Software:ehp8..
:eparml.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.3.01:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_CMDPROC._CMDPROC:elink.&colon. Returns
the name of the current command processor.
:eparml.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made prior to version 3.01:ehp8.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_APMAC._APMAC:elink.&colon. Advanced Power
Management AC line status.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_APMBATT._APMBATT:elink.&colon. Advanced
Power Management battery status.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_APMLIFE._APMLIFE:elink.&colon. Advanced
Power Management remaining battery life.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_CPU._CPU:elink.&colon. Now returns "686"
for Pentium Pro.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_DOWI._DOWI:elink.&colon. Returns the
current day of week as an integer (Sun = 1, Mon = 2, etc.).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_XPIXELS._XPIXELS:elink.&colon. Returns the
physical screen horizontal size in pixels.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_YPIXELS._YPIXELS:elink.&colon. Returns the
physical screen vertical size in pixels.
:eparml.
:p.
:p.
:lm margin=1.
Added or updated the following variable functions (all functions listed are
new unless otherwise noted)&colon.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made by JP Software:ehp8..
:eparml.
:lm margin=1.:parml tsize=10 break=fit.
:pt.:hp2.3.01:ehp2. :pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@EAWRITE.@EAWRITE:elink.[filename,EAname,[value]]&colon.
You can now delete an EA by specifying an empty third argument (i.e.,
"%@earead[filename,.subject,]).
:eparml.
:lm margin=8.:parml tsize=3 break=fit.
:pt.:hp8.The following changes were made prior to version 3.01:ehp8.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@CLIP.@CLIP:elink.[n]&colon. Returns line
:hp2.n:ehp2. from the clipboard (base 0).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@CONVERT.@CONVERT:elink.[input,output,value]&colon. Converts a
number from one base to another.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@DAY.@DAY:elink.[date]&colon. Returns the
day for the specified :hp2.date:ehp2.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@DOW.@DOW:elink.[date]&colon. Returns the
day of week for the specified :hp2.date:ehp2., as a string (Sun, Mon, etc.)
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@DOWI.@DOWI:elink.[date]&colon. Returns the
day of week for the specified :hp2.date:ehp2., as an integer (Sun = 1, Mon = 2, etc.).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@DOY.@DOY:elink.[date]&colon. Returns the
day of year for the specified :hp2.date:ehp2. (136).
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@EAREAD.@EAREAD:elink.[filename,EAname]&colon. Returns the specified
text extended attribute for the file.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@EAWRITE.@EAWRITE:elink.[filename,EAname,[value]]&colon. Writes the
specified text extended attribute for the file.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@EVAL.@EVAL:elink.[expression]&colon. Now
supports user-definable decimal and thousands characters; see :link reftype=hd
refid=INI_DecimalChar.DecimalChar:elink. and :link reftype=hd
refid=INI_ThousandsChar.ThousandsChar:elink., or :link reftype=hd
refid=SETDOS.SETDOS:elink. /G for details.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@EXEC.@EXEC:elink.[command]&colon. This
function has been modified; if you preface the :hp2.command:ehp2. with an '@', @EXEC
will return an empty string rather than the result code of the command.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@EXECSTR.@EXECSTR:elink.[command]&colon. Returns
the first line written to STDOUT by the specified command. (This is
intended to provide functionality similar to UNIX back-quoting.)
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@EXPAND.@EXPAND:elink.[filename[,attributes]]&colon. Expands a
wildcard filename and returns all of the matching filenames / directories on
a single line.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@FILEDATE.@FILEDATE:elink.[filename[,acw]]
/ :link reftype=hd
refid=_@FILETIME.@FILETIME:elink.[filename[,acw]]&colon. Added
the optional second argument determines which date / time field to return on
HPFS drives.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@FILESIZE.@FILESIZE:elink.[filename[,bkm[,a]]&colon. Added the
optional third argument :hp2.a:ehp2.(llocated); if specified, the function
returns the size actually used on disk, not the amount of data in the file.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@INSERT.@INSERT:elink.[n,string1,string2]&colon. Inserts
:hp2.string1:ehp2. into :hp2.string2:ehp2. starting at offset :hp2.n:ehp2.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@LEFT.@LEFT:elink.[n,string]&colon. Returns
the leftmost :hp2.n:ehp2. characters of :hp2.string:ehp2.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@MONTH.@MONTH:elink.[date]&colon. Return
the month for the specified :hp2.date:ehp2.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@NUMERIC.@NUMERIC:elink.[string]&colon. Now
considers a leading decimal separator as a numeric character, provided the
remainder of the :hp2.string:ehp2. is numeric and does not contain
additional decimal characters.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@REPLACE.@REPLACE:elink.[string1,string2,text]&colon. Replaces all
occurrences of :hp2.string1:ehp2. in text with :hp2.string2:ehp2.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@RIGHT.@RIGHT:elink.[n,string]&colon. Returns
the rightmost :hp2.n:ehp2. characters of :hp2.string:ehp2.&per.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@SEARCH.@SEARCH:elink.[filename[,path]]&colon. Now accepts an
optional second argument for the :hp2.path:ehp2. to search.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd
refid=_@SELECT.@SELECT:elink.[filename,top,left,bottom,right,title[,1]]&colon. Has
a new optional argument following the :hp2.title:ehp2.&per. If it's set to 1, @SELECT will
sort the list alphabetically.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@STRIP.@STRIP:elink.[chars,string]&colon. Return
:hp2.string:ehp2. with the characters in :hp2.chars:ehp2. removed.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@WILD.@WILD:elink.[string1,string2]&colon. Does
a wildcard comparison on the two strings and returns 1 if they match; 0 if
they don't.
:pt.:pd.:link reftype=hd refid=_@YEAR.@YEAR:elink.[date]&colon. Return the
year for the specified :hp2.date:ehp2.&per.
:eparml.

