:p.
:hp2.JFS:ehp2. or :hp2.Journaled File System:ehp2.&colon. A file
system distributed with OS/2 Warp 4 and above which allows
longer filenames, supports larger volumes, and provides better performance
than the traditional FAT16 filesystem. JFS logs filesystem changes in a
journal, which may drastically reduce the amount of time required to
verify and correct errors (disk checking).

