:p.
:hp2.Key Code:ehp2.&colon. The code passed to a program when a key is
pressed on the keyboard. depending upon the key that is pressed, and the
software handling the keyboard, the code can be an ASCII code, a scan code,
or an extended key code.
:p.
:hp2.Key Mapping:ehp2.&colon. A &4OS2. feature which allows you to assign new
keystrokes for command line functions such as manipulating the command
history or completing filenames.
:p.
:hp2.Keyboard Buffer:ehp2.&colon. A buffer which holds keystrokes you have
typed that have not yet been used by the currently executing program.
:p.
:hp2.Keystroke Alias:ehp2.&colon. An alias assigned to a key, so that it
can be invoked or recalled with a single keystroke.

