:p.
:p.
:hp2.Parameter:ehp2.&colon. A piece of additional information placed after
a command or function name. For example, in the command DIR XYZ, XYZ is a
parameter. Also used to refer to an alias parameter or batch file parameter.
:p.
:hp2.Parent Directory:ehp2.&colon. The directory in which a particular
subdirectory resides, often seen as the directory "above" a subdirectory.
:p.
:hp2.Parsing:ehp2.&colon. The process &4OS2. performs to analyze the command
line, perform alias and environment variable expansion, and find the
appropriate internal command or external command to execute. More
generally, the process of breaking down a string or message into its
individual components in order to process them properly.
:p.
:hp2.Passed Environment:ehp2.&colon. A copy of the master environment
created before running an application, so that any changes made by the
application will not affect the master environment.
:p.
:hp2.Path:ehp2.&colon. A specification of all the directories a file
resides in. For example, the path for
:hp1.C&colon.\WPFILES\MYDIR\MEMO.TXT:ehp1. is
:hp1.C&colon.\WPFILES\MYDIR\:ehp1.&per. Also used to refer to the environment
variable PATH, which contains a series of path
specifications used when searching for external commands and batch files.
:p.
:hp2.Pipe:ehp2.&colon. A method for collecting the standard output of one
program and passing it on as the standard input of the next program to be
executed, signified by a vertical bar "|" on the command line. See also
:hp2.Redirection:ehp2.&per.
:p.
:hp2.Previous Working Directory:ehp2.&colon. The working directory used
most recently, just prior to the current working directory. For example, if
:hp1.C&colon.\DATA :ehp1.is the current working directory and you switch to
:hp1.D&colon.\UTIL:ehp1., :hp1.C&colon.\DATA:ehp1. then becomes the previous
working directory.
:p.
:hp2.Primary Shell:ehp2.&colon. The copy of the character-mode command
processor which is loaded by the operating system when the system boots or a
session opens.

