:p.
:hp2.UCS-2:ehp2.&colon. The :hp2.Universal Coded Character Set:ehp2. (UCS, or
Unicode) is a standard set of characters defined by the International Standard
ISO/IEC 10646, Information technology ? Universal Coded Character Set (UCS),
utilizing 2 bytes for every character generated.
:p.
:hp2.UMB:ehp2. or :hp2.Upper Memory Block:ehp2.&colon. An XMS Upper Memory
Block, whose address is above the end of base memory (normally, above 640K),
but within the 1 megabyte of memory that DOS can address directly.
:p.
:hp2.UNC:ehp2. or :hp2.Universal Naming Convention:ehp2.&colon. A common
method for accessing files on a network drive without using a "mapped" drive
letter. Names specified this way are called UNC names, and typically appear
as :hp2.\\server\volume\path\filename:ehp2., where :hp2.server:ehp2. is the
name of the network server where the files reside, :hp2.volume :ehp2. is the
name of a disk volume on that server, and the :hp2.path\filename:ehp2.
portion is a directory name and filename.

