:p.
:hp2.Warm Reboot:ehp2.&colon. The process of restarting the computer with
software, or with the keyboard (:hp1.e.g. :ehp1.by pressing Ctrl-Alt-Del),
typically without physically resetting any hardware devices. See also
:hp2.Cold Reboot:ehp2.&per.
:p.
:hp2.White Space Character:ehp2.&colon. A character used to separate
arguments on the command line. The white space characters recognized by
&4OS2. are the space, tab, and comma.
:p.
:hp2.Wildcard:ehp2.&colon. A character ("*" or "?") used in a filename to
specify the possibility that any single character ("?") or sequence of
characters ("*") can occur at that point in the actual name. See also
:hp2.Extended Wildcard:ehp2.&per.
:p.
